The paper deals with a problem of misperceived label space in supervised learning, which is a common issue in machine learning. The proposed approach involves actively augmenting the feature space to discover potentially unknown labels, which falls under the category of exploratory machine learning. This approach can be applied to various domains such as computer vision (cs.CV), natural language processing (cs.CL), and cybersecurity (cs.CR). The paper also mentions the use of rejection models, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Overall, the paper's focus on machine learning and its applications in various domains makes it likely to belong to the cs.LG category.
